Provenance and third-party material for rtransparency
=====================================================

rtransparency is released under the GNU General Public License v3 (see the
LICENSE file). It is a renamed, enhanced fork that builds on existing GPL-3
work; this file records that provenance for redistribution. All components
below are GPL-3 compatible, so the combined package remains under GPL-3. No
upstream copyright notice has been removed.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. rtransparent (the tool this package builds on)
   Source:  https://github.com/serghiou/rtransparent
   Paper:   https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pbio.3001107
   Author:  Stylianos Serghiou
   License: GPL-3
   Use:     rtransparency began as a fork of rtransparent and reuses and extends
            its conflict-of-interest, funding and registration detectors.
            Stylianos Serghiou is credited as an author in DESCRIPTION.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. metareadr
   Source:  https://github.com/serghiou/metareadr
   Author:  Stylianos Serghiou
   License: GPL-3
   Use:     the internal, benchmark-only NCBI PMC OAI-PMH fallback used to fetch
            full-text XML (R/rt_fetch.R) is adapted from
            metareadr::mt_read_pmcoa(). Not part of the detector pipeline.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The package no longer contains any code copied from the AGPL-licensed oddpub
package; data and code sharing detection is implemented natively. The full text
of the GPL-3 license is in the LICENSE file and at
https://spdx.org/licenses/GPL-3.0-only.html.
